## Summary

Found a **case-sensitivity bug** in `bs4.filter.SoupStrainer` ✅

**Bug**: SoupStrainer performs case-sensitive attribute matching while HTML parsers convert attribute names to lowercase. This causes strainers with uppercase attribute names (e.g., `CLASS`, `ID`) to never match parsed HTML tags.

**Impact**: Users creating strainers with uppercase attribute names will get unexpected empty results when searching HTML documents.

**Bug report saved**: `bug_report_bs4_filter_2025-08-18_20-24_zfui.md`

Tested 10 properties total:
- ✅ 7 properties passed (MatchRule behaviors work correctly)
- ❌ 1 real bug found (attribute case sensitivity)
- 📝 2 test issues fixed (my test assumptions were incorrect)
